{"TopicId":146376,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"KSP without sound","CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T21:04:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T21:04:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not really a bug or issue, but maybe a way to track one down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to run KSP without any sound at all?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot just muted but with sound totally turned off (without removing every sound device from my computer).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike a switch to KSP/Unity to ignore audio?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP64/win10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-22T21:07:47Z\u0022 title=\u002208/22/2016 09:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 22, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Curveball Anders\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T21:26:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222725842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471899859\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is not really a bug or issue, but maybe a way to track one down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to run KSP without any sound at all?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot just muted but with sound totally turned off (without removing every sound device from my computer).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike a switch to KSP/Unity to ignore audio?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP64/win10\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. Settings \u0026gt; Sounds \u0026gt; turn off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T21:28:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222725864\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471901199\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158329\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrbitalBuzzsaw\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, OrbitalBuzzsaw said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah. Settings \u0026gt; Sounds \u0026gt; turn off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut doesn\u0027t that turn the sound down to zero while still running the audio processing thread?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy hunch is that there\u0027s a thread de-sync, and I want to test it by removing that thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-22T21:30:06Z\u0022 title=\u002208/22/2016 09:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 22, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Curveball Anders\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrbitalBuzzsaw","CreatedById":158329,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-23T00:10:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222725868\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471901310\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut doesn\u0027t that turn the sound down to zero while still running the audio processing thread?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy hunch is that there\u0027s a thread de-sync, and I want to test it by removing that thread.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSay what now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-23T00:25:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222726068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146376\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471911021\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158329\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrbitalBuzzsaw\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, OrbitalBuzzsaw said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSay what now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP has been reported to crash, even it hasn\u0027t for me until the last 4 days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to track down why, and since it\u0027s crashing in j.random scene and even randomly after being in the background for an hour or two.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRandom crashes in software, esp with no user input, is very likely to be a thread de-sync, and since sound/audio is handed off to a thread of it\u0027s own I\u0027d like to eliminate that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-23T10:02:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think this is possible Curveball, sorry, there doesn\u0027t appear to be a means to disable sound like there is for graphics ( -nographics and -batchmode )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}